>> title: Creamy Cashew Alfredo
>> cuisine: Italian
>> tags: sauce, vegan, gluten-free, soy-free
>> servings: 6
>> yield: 3 cups
>> storage_days: 5
>> storage_method: refrigerated
>> reheat: Reheat with splash of coconut milk, whisk.

Soak @raw cashews{1%cup} in boiling water for ~{15%minutes}. Drain.

Blend drained cashews, @full-fat coconut milk{1%can} (13.5 oz), @nutritional yeast{1/4%cup}, @fresh lemon juice{3%tbsp}, @garlic{4%cloves}(minced), @kosher salt{1%tsp}, @black pepper{1/2%tsp}, and @nutmeg{1/4%tsp} in #blender{} until completely smooth.

Transfer to #saucepan{}. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened ~{5-7%minutes}.

Taste and adjust seasoning.

Thin with more coconut milk if needed.

Garnish with @fresh basil{} or @fresh parsley{} when serving.

-- Rich, creamy pasta sauce without the dairy
